/**
 * Render-audit harness (uncommitted working tool).
 *
 * Drives every item‚Üítext render path in the lowering pipeline's render.ts, plus
 * the channel's context preamble and the MCP self-description strings, with
 * representative inputs, and emits the ACTUAL rendered output for each case as
 * one markdown document ‚Äî so the audit reviews real outputs side by side
 * instead of spelunking the code.
 *
 * The annotate-iterate loop:
 *  - output goes to <repo>/audit.local/render-audit.md (gitignored via *.local)
 *  - every case ends with a `**Comments:**` block; the owner writes decisions
 *    there in place, and the agent reads them back to drive code changes
 *  - each run first backs up the existing file to render-audit.v<N>.md, so an
 *    annotated round survives regeneration and `diff v<N> render-audit.md`
 *    shows exactly what a code change did to the outputs
 *
 * Run: pnpm exec tsx render-audit.mts [output.md]   (from this package dir)
 */
